- "Intensity" refers to the severity level of the weather condition, where a higher number indicates a more severe condition.;
- "Sparked alerts" means that the weather condition has led to the issuance of at least one alert.

- "Most common weather condition" refers to the weather condition that appears most frequently in the records for each station and date;
- "Weather station" is a facility where meteorological data is collected and recorded;
- "Date" refers to the day on which the weather data was collected.

